5.2 The Personal LLM

Architecture:

· Base Model: Pruned version of open-source 7B parameter model
· Fine-tuning: Continual learning from user interactions (with consent)
· Size Variants:
  · Edge version: 300M parameters (runs on Relay)
  · Personal node: 1B parameters (home server)
  · Full version: 7B parameters (when connected to cloud)

Privacy Features:

```python
class PrivateLearning:
    def learn_from_interaction(self, data):
        # Federated learning principles
        if not self.consent_manager.has_consent("learning"):
            return "NO_CONSENT"
        
        # Differential privacy guarantees
        noise = self.generate_dp_noise(epsilon=0.1)
        processed = data + noise
        
        # Local training only
        self.model.train_local(processed)
        
        # Only send anonymized gradients (optional)
        if self.consent_manager.has_consent("improvement"):
            gradients = self.model.get_gradients()
            anonymized = self.anonymize(gradients)
            self.send_to_cloud(anonymized)
        
        return "LEARNED_LOCALLY"
```

5.3 Context Engine

Multi-dimensional Context Tracking:

1. Temporal Context: Time of day, calendar, routines
2. Spatial Context: Location, movement, proximity to others
3. Social Context: Who's nearby, relationship, social norms
4. Physiological Context: Stress level, energy, attention capacity
5. Task Context: Current goal, progress, obstacles

Context Prediction:

· 85% accuracy in predicting user needs 5 minutes ahead
· Adaptive privacy: Reduces data collection when in sensitive locations
· Cross-context learning: Learns that "tired after work" means different needs than "tired before work"

5.4 Orchestration Engine

Intelligent Task Routing:

```python
class OrchestrationEngine:
    def route_task(self, task, context):
        # Evaluate constraints
        constraints = {
            'privacy': task.privacy_requirement,
            'latency': task.max_latency,
            'energy': context.battery_levels,
            'cost': user.cost_preference,
            'accuracy': task.accuracy_needed
        }
        
        # Available nodes
        nodes = self.discovery.find_nodes(constraints)
        
        # Optimal routing decision
        if constraints['privacy'] == 'HIGH':
            return nodes.local  # Process on personal device
        elif constraints['latency'] < 100:  # ms
            return nodes.edge  # Process on Relay
        elif task.compute_intensive:
            return nodes.cloud  # Use cloud resources
        else:
            # Cost-optimized routing
            return self.cost_optimizer.select(nodes)
```

5.5 Haptic Language Standardization

64-Pattern Vocabulary organized into categories:

1. Navigation (8 patterns):
   · Forward/back/left/right pulses
   · Distance indicators (closer = faster pulses)
   · Arrival confirmation (three short pulses)
2. Notifications (16 patterns):
   · Urgency levels (1-5 pulses)
   · Source identification (family vs work vs system)
   · Response requests (yes/no/question patterns)
3. Emotional Communication (12 patterns):
   · Calming (slow waves)
   · Alerting (sharp pulses)
   · Affection (gentle warmth simulation)
   · Concern (irregular gentle pulses)
4. Health Feedback (8 patterns):
   · Medication reminders
   · Posture correction
   · Stress level indication
   · Hydration reminders
5. System Status (20 patterns):
   · Battery levels
   · Network connectivity
   · Authentication status
   · Error conditions

Learning System: Patterns adapt to user sensitivity over first 30 days of use.

