12. RISKS & MITIGATIONS

12.1 Technical Risks

Risk Probability Impact Mitigation
Battery tech doesn't improve Medium High Multiple battery chemistries in development; supercapacitor backup
NLP not accurate enough for dialects High Medium Crowdsourced data collection with incentives; fallback to simpler commands
SyncMesh protocol vulnerabilities Low Critical Formal verification; bug bounty up to $1M; gradual deployment
Hardware failure rates >5% Medium High Redundant design; easy replacement; generous warranty

12.2 Market Risks

Risk Probability Impact Mitigation
Incumbents copy key features Low High They can't without destroying business models; patent portfolio
User reluctance to change Medium Medium Phased transition (smartphone companion first); strong value prop
Regulatory blockade Low Critical Early regulator engagement; compliance by design; multiple jurisdictions
Partner dependencies High Medium Multiple partners in each category; open protocols reduce lock-in

12.3 Ethical & Social Risks

Risk Probability Impact Mitigation
Perception as surveillance tool Medium High Transparent design; third-party audits; open-source core
Digital divide widening Low High Radical pricing; offline functionality; literacy-free design
Addiction transfer (from screen to ear) Medium Medium Attention metrics as KPIs; "quiet hours" enforced
Algorithmic bias High High Continuous auditing; diverse training data; bias correction

12.4 Financial Risks

Risk Probability Impact Mitigation
Hardware cost reductions slower Medium Medium Multiple suppliers; design simplification; accept lower margins initially
Subscription unwillingness High Medium Tiered model (free basic); value demonstration; micro-payments
Currency fluctuations High Medium Local pricing; hedging; multi-currency operations
Funding winter Medium High 24-month runway always; government grants; strategic investors

